Remove and loops that merged together from import and self loops

full = subsetLoops(full, full@rowData$loopWidth >= 5000)
full = removeSelfLoops(full)
full_corrected = mangoCorrection(full, FDR = 0.05)
dim(full_corrected)

Now lets filter the loops that have >= 5 PETs in one Rep but 0 in the other

cm <- full_corrected@counts
EBNA3COff <- ((cm[,3]>=2 &cm[,4]==0)|(cm[,4]>=2&cm[,3]==0))
EBNA3COn <- ((cm[,5]>=2 &cm[,6]==0)|(cm[,6]>=2&cm[,5]==0))
qc_filt <- subsetLoops(full_corrected, !(EBNA3COff | EBNA3COn))
dim(qc_filt)

Filtering complete, lets look at sample quality

p1 = loopDistancePlot(qc_filt)

Lets split out the edgeR differential loops, this may make it better! First, annotate the peaks based on enhancer, promoter and CTCF Enhancer: ChromHMM Annotated Enhancers +/- 2kb Promoter: TSS +/- 2kb CTCF: CTCF peaks +/- 500bp ** Need to remove chr for annotateLoops to work **

enhancerbed = "wgEncodeBroadHmmGm12878HMM_Enhancer.bed"
ctcfbed = "ENCFF833FTF.CTCF.bed"

enhancer = rmchr(padGRanges(bedToGRanges(enhancerbed), pad = 2000))
promoter <- rmchr(padGRanges(getHumanTSS(), pad = 2000)) # +/- 2kb
ctcf = rmchr(padGRanges(bedToGRanges(ctcfbed), pad = 500))
# Annotate the qcLoops object
seqlevels(qc_filt@anchors) <- gsub('chr','',seqlevels(qc_filt@anchors))
seqlevels(qcLoops_edgeR@anchors) <- gsub('chr','',seqlevels(qcLoops_edgeR@anchors))
km_anno <- annotateLoops(qcLoops_edgeR, enhancer = enhancer, promoter = promoter, ctcf = ctcf)
